# TV HUD — positions & alignment

Samsung Q6F QLED 4K kiosk at `/`. **Do not change viewport, slideshow breakpoints, or widget order** unless the user asks.

## Layout (pre-PR style)

| Element | Rule |
|---------|------|
| Widget anchor | `.tv-hud-widgets` — `position: absolute`, `bottom: 36px`, `left/right: 48px`, `text-align: right` |
| Stack | `.tv-hud-widget-stack` — `display: inline-block`, `vertical-align: bottom`, `text-align: left` |
| Weather row | `.tv-hud-weather` flex; cards `flex: 1 1 220px`, `min-width: 220px`, `margin-left: 16px` (first card `margin-left: 0`) |
| Full-width cards | `.tv-hud-earthquake` / `.tv-hud-binance` — inner `.tv-widget-card` `width: 100%`, `margin-left: 0` |
| Stack spacing | Single `--tv-hud-gap` (24px / 28px @1600+) for row `margin-bottom` **and** `.tv-hud-widgets` `bottom` |
| Overflow | `.tv-gallery` + `body.tv-body-gallery.tv-kiosk` use `overflow: visible` so the weather row is not clipped; `.tv-slideshow` keeps `overflow: hidden` |
| Tizen cards | No `backdrop-filter` on gallery `.tv-widget-card` (M56 clips the top edge); use solid `var(--card-bg)` |
| Dark HUD | `theme-night` always; datetime always `#fff` |

## Stack order (mandatory)

weather → earthquake → binance in `templates/core/tv_dashboard.html`.

## Structure

```
.tv-hud (full screen overlay)
  .tv-hud-datetime (absolute top-left)
  .tv-hud-widgets (bottom-right anchor)
    .tv-hud-widget-stack (inline-block)
      .tv-hud-weather (flex row, two cards)
      .tv-hud-earthquake (full width card)
      .tv-hud-binance (full width card)
```

## Do not

- Flex-center the whole HUD column on the right (Tizen `margin-left: auto` / `left: auto` issues)
- Fixed pixel column width (`--tv-hud-widget-width`) that constrains the weather row artificially
- `.tv-hud-widget-slot` wrappers — use `.tv-hud-weather` / `.tv-hud-earthquake` / `.tv-hud-binance` directly
- Day theme on gallery HUD
